WEBVTT

00:10.008 --> 00:15.441
So many couples wanted to be married on Sunday, the first day of legal homosexual marriage in New York City,...

00:16.116 --> 00:19.270
...that local officials announced a lottery to determine eligibility.

00:20.424 --> 00:23.986
New York City Council Speaker Christine Quinn, herself openly gay,...

00:24.478 --> 00:26.405
...witnessed the first two ceremonies.

00:26.894 --> 00:30.369
She says the same-sex marriage law supports equality.

00:31.647 --> 00:36.803
Margie Phelps minced no words to denounce same-sex marriage as a crime against God.

00:37.679 --> 00:41.520
She and other Christians from the Westboro Baptist Church in Topeka, Kansas...

00:41.940 --> 00:45.792
...came halfway across the country to say marriage is defined by Holy Scripture.

00:46.751 --> 00:53.749
David Schwartz, an Orthodox Jew, believes every human being has free choice and the power to rule over their desires.

00:54.373 --> 00:56.858
He considers homosexual desire to be wrong.

00:57.235 --> 01:01.027
Gella Soloman, also a Jew, rejects that definition of marriage,...

01:01.421 --> 01:05.606
...as well as the notion that marriage is reserved for the procreation of children.

01:05.960 --> 01:09.898
Douglas Robinson and his partner of 25 years, Michael Elsasser,...

01:10.327 --> 01:12.536
...were in the first group to be married in Manhattan.

01:13.340 --> 01:20.467
Robinson says the United States allows religious views to coexist with what he believes is a civil right of same-sex marriage.

01:21.153 --> 01:26.465
Margie Phelps believes God will punish New York City for permitting what she believes to be moral decay.

01:27.401 --> 01:31.832
Meanwhile, Nevin Cohen and Daniel Hernandez showed off their marriage certificates.

01:32.542 --> 01:34.741
But they said they are not going on a honeymoon.

01:35.416 --> 01:37.448
They say they need to be at work on Monday.

01:38.223 --> 01:40.554
Peter Fedynsky, VOA News, New York.

